🎮 Game Development
Unity → Main game engine (recommended for Android games).

Blender → For creating or editing custom 3D models (shops, decorations).

Figma → For designing UI wireframes and mockups.

Unity Asset Store → Ready-made assets (shops, buildings, skins).

☁️ Backend & Cloud
Firebase → Authentication, database (Firestore), analytics, dynamic links (for invites).

PlayFab (Microsoft) → Leaderboards, events, player data management.

💰 Monetization
Google AdMob → Rewarded ads, interstitial ads, banners.

Google Play Billing Library → In-app purchases (premium shops, skins, event passes).

🌍 Social & Viral Features
Firebase Dynamic Links → Friend invites with referral rewards.

Unity Social Sharing Plugins → Share screenshots directly to WhatsApp, Instagram, TikTok.

📊 Testing & Analytics
Firebase Analytics → Track retention, ad engagement, purchases.

Unity Test Tools → Debugging and performance testing.

Google Play Console → Beta testing, app publishing, performance reports.

🚀 Publishing & Marketing
Google Play Console → Upload APK, manage releases, handle reviews.

Canva / Figma → Create Play Store screenshots, promo images, and banners.

Social Media (Instagram, TikTok, Twitter) → Marketing and viral growth.

✅ With this stack, you can:

Build the game in Unity.

Manage backend with Firebase + PlayFab.

Monetize via AdMob + Play Billing.

Add virality with Dynamic Links + Social Sharing.

Publish and grow via Google Play Console + social media marketing.
